<subsection>
    <title>Transformations of Functions</title>

    <definition>
        <title>transformation</title>

        <statement>
            <p>
                <alert>Transformations</alert> are rule-based <em>changes</em> to the graph of a function. Each transformation can occur in one of two directions: <em>vertical</em> or <em>horizontal</em>. There are three types of transformations:
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <em>Translation</em>- This represents a change in <em>location</em>.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <em>Dilation</em>- This represents a change in <em>size</em>.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <em>Reflection</em>- This represents a change in <em>orientation</em>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>

    <p>
        Given a function <m>f(x)</m>, a transformation of <m>f(x)</m> is a function of the form
    </p>

    <p>
    </p>

    <p>
        \arraystretch2
    </p>

